set up, I can move forward with the invocation and assert it properly. It's all about clear and efficient execution!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code structure**\\n\\nI don’t need to reflect directly, but I'm thinking about how to import necessary classes. I could consider combining methods and making everything top-level public. Also, how should I handle checkstyle line lengths? I need to keep them under 120 characters, with any existing splits taken into account. I think using AssertJ could be beneficial, and I definitely need to make sure I write everything out properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qHwDDjJyMiBdkuArZFbPk8KS|fc_00f2c3a55c4148800169fd52979a40819ea4f311cdea001a81", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.fluentlenium/fluentlenium-core/6.0.0/src/test/java/io_fluentlenium/fluentlenium_core/MessageProxyTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_fluentlenium.fluentlenium_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.Negation;\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.message.Message;\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.message.MessageBuilderCall;\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.message.MessageContext;\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.message.MessageProxy;\nimport io.fluentlenium.core.conditions.message.NotMessage;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class MessageProxyTest {\n    @Test\n    void builderWithContextCreatesProxyThatRecordsAnnotatedCalls() {\n        MessageCondition condition = MessageProxy.builder(MessageCondition.class, \"field name\");\n\n        boolean result = condition.equalTo(\"value\");\n\n        assertThat(result).isFalse();\n        assertThat(MessageProxy.message(condition)).isEqualTo(\"field name is not equal to value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void builderWithCallsCreatesProxyUsingExistingCallStack() {\n        List<MessageBuilderCall> calls = new ArrayList<>();\n        MessageBuilderCall initialCall = new MessageBuilderCall();\n        initialCall.setContext(\"existing context\");\n        calls.add(initialCall);\n        MessageCondition condition = MessageProxy.builder(MessageCondition.class, calls);\n\n        MessageCondition contextualCondition = condition.withElementContext();\n        contextualCondition.equalTo(\"item\");\n\n        assertThat(MessageProxy.message(contextualCondition)).isEqualTo(\"existing context element is not equal to item\");\n        assertThat(calls).hasSize(3);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void wrapWithContextCreatesProxyThatInvokesOriginalInstance() {\n        RecordingCondition instance = new RecordingCondition(true);\n        MessageCondition condition = MessageProxy.wrap(MessageCondition.class, instance, \"wrapped field\");\n\n        boolean result = condition.equalTo(\"actual\");\n\n        assertThat(result).isTrue();\n        assertThat(instance.comparedValue()).isEqualTo(\"actual\");\n        assertThat(MessageProxy.message(condition)).isEqualTo(\"wrapped field is not equal to actual\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void wrapWithCallsCreatesProxyThatSharesRecordedCallsWithOriginalInstance() {\n        List<MessageBuilderCall> calls = new ArrayList<>();\n        MessageBuilderCall initialCall = new MessageBuilderCall();\n        initialCall.setContext(\"shared context\");\n        calls.add(initialCall);\n        RecordingCondition instance = new RecordingCondition(false);\n        MessageCondition condition = MessageProxy.wrap(MessageCondition.class, instance, calls);\n\n        MessageCondition negatedCondition = condition.not();\n        boolean result = negatedCondition.equalTo(\"other\");\n\n        assertThat(result).isFalse();\n        assertThat(instance.notCalls()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(instance.comparedValue()).isEqualTo(\"other\");\n        assertThat(MessageProxy.message(negatedCondition)).isEqualTo(\"shared context is equal to other\");\n        assertThat(calls).hasSize(3);\n    }\n\n    public interface MessageCondition {\n        @MessageContext(\"element\")\n        MessageCondition withElementContext();\n\n        @Negation\n        MessageCondition not();\n\n        @Message(\"is equal to {0}\")\n        @NotMessage(\"is not equal to {0}\")\n        boolean equalTo(String value);\n    }\n\n    public static final class RecordingCondition implements MessageCondition {\n        private final boolean comparisonResult;\n        private String comparedValue;\n        private int notCalls;\n\n        RecordingCondition(boolean comparisonResult) {\n            this.comparisonResult = comparisonResult;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public MessageCondition withElementContext() {\n            return this;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public MessageCondition not() {\n            notCalls++;\n            return this;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean equalTo(String value) {\n            comparedValue = value;\n            return comparisonResult;\n        }\n\n        String comparedValue() {\n            return comparedValue;\n        }\n\n        int notCalls() {\n            return notCalls;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 289, "output": 1836, "cacheRead": 15360, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17485, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778209417274, "responseId": "resp_00f2c3a55c4148800169fd5289a484819eb98222d788f2c576"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_qHwDDjJyMiBdkuArZFbPk8KS|fc_00f2c3a55c4148800169fd52979a40819ea4f311cdea001a81", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"t